Datatype.Name: WhiteSpaceFacetCodeSimpleType
Datatype.DefinitionText: A data type for a data type for a specification of white space for a data type.

Enumeration.DefinitionText: No normalization is done, the value is not changed (this is the behavior required by [XML 1.0 (Second Edition)] for element content)
All occurrences of #x9 (tab), #xA (line feed) and #xD (carriage return) are replaced with #x20 (space)
After the processing implied by replace, contiguous sequences of #x20's are collapsed to a single #x20, and leading and trailing #x20's are removed.
